Next, we will solve for the price of the stock at Year 4. To do this, we will use this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Share price at Year 4}&=\dfrac{\text{Expected dividend}\times (1+\text{Growth rate})}{\text{Required rate of return} \times \text{Growth rate}}
\end{aligned}$$

Substituting the values, we will get:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Share price at Year 4}&=\dfrac{\$5.03\times1.05}{0.12-0.05}\\[15 pt]
&=\$75.45
\end{aligned}$$
